I tried to rc, team, update on my cvs source tree but eclipse returned with a
dialog saying "Malformed entry line, missing revision: ".  I then tried to
replace with latest and I received the same error.  Finally I deleted my source
tree and then went to the cvs browsing window and checked out src back into my
current project.  Finally that allowed me to build.

The only thing we can do without a reproducable test is to find the place in 
the code where the failure occurs and see if we can improve the error message. 
In this case, we should print the entry line along with the resource path so we 
could at least see which resource the problem happened for.

We were not able to reproduce this and nothing in the stacktrace indicates CVS 
so there's nothing we can do.
